description:
D4.2 VERITY Protocol Dataset&nbsp; serves as the empirical foundation of the VERITY Protocol, incorporating a qualitative content analysis of VERITY materials to generate  VERITY recommendations for strengthening public trust in science . The original VERITY texts were systematically coded by assigning labels to text fragments within the dataset.&nbsp; 


 The coding process covered 11 fields, combining both open-ended responses and structured drop-down lists. The drop-down categories for &lsquo;Stewards of Trust&rsquo; (eight SOT categories) and &lsquo;Recommendations&rsquo; (six recommendation categories) were derived from previous VERITY research, particularly D4.1 VERITY Synthesis Report, and were refined iteratively during the coding phase, as detailed in D4.2 The VERITY Protocol.&nbsp; 


 Three researchers conducted the coding process, following a training session before its initiation. Inter-coder reliability was ensured through regular team meetings and cross-checks of the dataset. The full dataset comprises 556 lines of recommendations, each designed to enhance public trust in science and tailored to different Stewards of Trust.&nbsp;

